I'm doomed. How am I supposed to go to school now?

501
00:48:28,840 --> 00:48:30,800
Oh my goodness!

502
00:48:36,260 --> 00:48:38,250
Are you okay?

503
00:48:38,250 --> 00:48:40,720
Not even my mother hit me,

504
00:48:40,720 --> 00:48:42,180
but I got hit by Yeon Woo.

505
00:48:42,180 --> 00:48:45,150
Oh no. Let me see.

506
00:48:46,860 --> 00:48:48,300
I'm okay.

507
00:48:48,300 --> 00:48:50,620
Let's go to the nurse's office.

508
00:48:57,710 --> 00:49:00,420
The nurse is not here again.

509
00:49:00,420 --> 00:49:02,440
Have a seat here.

510
00:49:20,270 --> 00:49:22,920
Since there is a mirror, do you want to put it on yourself?

511
00:49:22,920 --> 00:49:26,160
You're not going to put it on me?

512
00:49:26,160 --> 00:49:29,290
I'd be more of a nuisance if I faint from a color rush.

513
00:49:29,290 --> 00:49:32,520
No, you wouldn't be.

514
00:49:33,990 --> 00:49:37,560
Then, just a little.

515
00:50:08,400 --> 00:50:11,620
It seems I won't faint from this much exposure.

516
00:50:11,620 --> 00:50:14,430
I can take it off if you tell me to.

517
00:50:15,990 --> 00:50:17,910
I'm going to put it on.

518
00:50:19,380 --> 00:50:21,080
Does it hurt a lot?

519
00:50:21,080 --> 00:50:22,980
Blow on it for me.

520
00:50:33,190 --> 00:50:34,870
Are you okay?

521
00:50:34,870 --> 00:50:36,610
Yeah...

522
00:50:45,200 --> 00:50:49,220
Ye-llow.

523
00:50:49,220 --> 00:50:54,350
[Missing person | Mono, Yoo Yi Ri]

524
00:50:55,880 --> 00:50:57,810
Yeon Woo.

525
00:50:59,620 --> 00:51:03,330
[Nurse's Office]

526
00:51:05,730 --> 00:51:07,590
Are you okay?

527
00:51:19,210 --> 00:51:21,490
What the...

528
00:51:21,490 --> 00:51:23,580
Why am I like this?

529
00:51:25,930 --> 00:51:28,430
You were crying a lot.

530
00:51:28,430 --> 00:51:33,770
You suddenly started writhing in pain and cried

531
00:51:33,770 --> 00:51:36,640
but you looked unconscious.

532
00:51:36,640 --> 00:51:39,790
What exactly did I do?

533
00:51:39,790 --> 00:51:42,000
I don't remember.

534
00:51:43,950 --> 00:51:46,000
I can't...

535
00:51:48,180 --> 00:51:50,010
see color.

536
00:51:50,810 --> 00:51:54,840
Don't you remember... the decoloring?

537
00:51:54,840 --> 00:52:00,320
You wanted to see the color of the headband and didn't want the color to fade.

538
00:52:08,190 --> 00:52:12,420
The experience... already past?

539
00:52:14,720 --> 00:52:19,650
That is something Monos experience as they are adjusting to their Probe.

540
00:52:19,650 --> 00:52:24,290
You can experience an extended color rush, a blackout, delayed fainting spell,

541
00:52:24,290 --> 00:52:26,120
and your subconscious can emerge.

542
00:52:26,120 --> 00:52:31,820
Then, it's a good sign that he's adjusting, right?

543
00:52:35,610 --> 00:52:37,820
Regardless, stop doing this at school.

544
00:52:37,820 --> 00:52:40,850
He's already so thin and pale looking.

545
00:52:40,850 --> 00:52:42,560
I understand.

546
00:52:52,410 --> 00:52:56,870
It's a relief to hear that you're adjusting. I was very surprised.

547
00:52:56,870 --> 00:52:59,730
I'm adjusting? To what?

548
00:52:59,730 --> 00:53:02,750
Me? To the Probe?

549
00:53:02,750 --> 00:53:04,850
To Go Yoo Han?

550
00:53:05,760 --> 00:53:07,820
Yeon Woo.

551
00:53:07,820 --> 00:53:11,960
What happens after I adjust? Obsession?

552
00:53:11,960 --> 00:53:15,580
Kidnapping? Murder?

553
00:53:15,580 --> 00:53:17,780
Look at me.

554
00:53:39,290 --> 00:53:41,220
You need to wash your face.

555
00:53:41,220 --> 00:53:46,180
You look pretty even when you're disheveled, but it's so obvious you cried.

556
00:53:58,800 --> 00:54:03,750
I'm the Mono! Why are you the one keeping me from running away?

557
00:54:04,560 --> 00:54:06,330
Go Yoo Han.

558
00:54:07,860 --> 00:54:10,510
♫ Hug me so ♫

559
00:54:10,510 --> 00:54:12,770
Why are you crying when I'm the one who blacked out?

560
00:54:12,770 --> 00:54:15,130
Earlier, I thought something bad happened to you...

561
00:54:15,130 --> 00:54:17,890
♫  I won't fall  ♫

562
00:54:17,890 --> 00:54:19,550
and I was so scared.

563
00:54:19,550 --> 00:54:22,120
I understand, so let me go.

564
00:54:22,120 --> 00:54:23,720
I don't want to.

565
00:54:23,720 --> 00:54:29,810
Since it's raining... just for a bit.

566
00:54:29,810 --> 00:54:32,260
What does that have to do with hugging me?

567
00:54:32,260 --> 00:54:34,050
♫ Even if I'm far away ♫

568
00:54:34,050 --> 00:54:36,220
I now know

569
00:54:36,220 --> 00:54:41,770
that what my heart desires is different from what is rational.

570
00:54:41,770 --> 00:54:44,820
It's nice being with my Probe.

571
00:54:44,820 --> 00:54:46,280
I want to see color.

572
00:54:46,280 --> 00:54:50,070
Do you want to see the color I see?

573
00:54:50,070 --> 00:54:52,620
Yes.

574
00:54:52,620 --> 00:54:54,580
What?

575
00:54:54,580 --> 00:54:58,030
This jerk! Can he tell what I'm thinking?

576
00:54:58,030 --> 00:55:02,040
Yeon Woo, look forward.

577
00:55:02,040 --> 00:55:06,110
♫  I'm going to confess to you now  ♫

578
00:55:06,110 --> 00:55:12,180
Since I'm your Probe, the color I know will be the color you know,

579
00:55:12,180 --> 00:55:16,600
and we will be seeing the same colors.

580
00:55:16,600 --> 00:55:18,680
What are you talking about?

581
00:55:18,680 --> 00:55:24,010
So if you say the river is the color of the sea, then it's the color of the sea and if you say it's the color of the water, then it's the color of the water?

582
00:55:24,010 --> 00:55:27,730
Yes, that's how it will be.

583
00:55:27,730 --> 00:55:29,060
That's ridiculous.

584
00:55:29,060 --> 00:55:31,110
♫  These nights shine even more because you're here  ♫

585
00:55:31,110 --> 00:55:36,240
For some reason, I saw my happiness fading away the moment I felt happy.

586
00:55:36,240 --> 00:55:38,580
♫ That's the only reason  ♫

587
00:55:38,580 --> 00:55:43,100
♫ In this quiet moment, I'll fall asleep  ♫

588
00:55:43,100 --> 00:55:47,000
Loss. When everything fades,

589
00:55:47,000 --> 00:55:50,750
and I only have moments of happiness in a gray space alone,

590
00:55:50,750 --> 00:55:54,520
that's terrifying and horrible. If only I could stop happiness

591
00:55:54,520 --> 00:55:57,260
from escaping me.

592
00:55:57,260 --> 00:55:59,580
If only I...

593
00:55:59,580 --> 00:56:01,430
Choi Yeon Woo!

594
00:56:01,430 --> 00:56:03,680
Let go of me!

595
00:56:03,680 --> 00:56:06,090
What were you just thinking, Choi Yeon Woo?

596
00:56:06,090 --> 00:56:08,560
Why are you acting like this?

597
00:56:09,600 --> 00:56:15,100
I had the thought... that I wanted to lock you up.

598
00:56:15,100 --> 00:56:19,410
♫  I'll find you no matter where you are  ♫

599
00:56:19,410 --> 00:56:25,820
♫  I never once forgot any of those days  ♫

600
00:56:25,820 --> 00:56:31,150
♫  The words I kept to myself  ♫

601
00:56:37,470 --> 00:56:39,380
Go Yoo Han said he won't make it to school today.

602
00:56:39,380 --> 00:56:40,520
Why are you telling me that?

603
00:56:40,520 --> 00:56:43,460
He told me to tell you.

604
00:56:43,460 --> 00:56:46,680
He said it in a way that made me not want to tell you, but that's what he basically said.

605
00:56:46,680 --> 00:56:50,100
He told me to tell you that he can't come today.

606
00:56:50,100 --> 00:56:54,640
He could've just told me directly. Why did he ask Jung Joo Haeng to tell me?

607
00:56:54,640 --> 00:56:57,990
- Choi Yeon Woo!
- Let go!

608
00:56:57,990 --> 00:57:00,420
Why are you acting like this?

609
00:57:00,420 --> 00:57:02,360
I had the thought

610
00:57:03,880 --> 00:57:06,780
that I wanted to lock you up.

611
00:57:10,270 --> 00:57:14,460
He must be avoiding me. He realized the dangers of a Mono.

612
00:57:14,460 --> 00:57:18,860
I didn't want to know, but he's using me because I'm the class president.

613
00:57:18,860 --> 00:57:21,680
I really don't want to know.

614
00:57:21,680 --> 00:57:25,560
Gosh! I'm suffering from being friends with someone like him.

615
00:57:25,560 --> 00:57:28,430
Hey, Yeon Woo. Can you hold this? Hurry.

616
00:57:28,430 --> 00:57:30,860
Hurry up and come over here.

617
00:57:33,560 --> 00:57:36,020
- Like this?
-Yeah.

618
00:57:39,720 --> 00:57:41,700
Let me see...

619
00:57:43,350 --> 00:57:46,690
- How is it? It's perfect, right?
- Yeah.

620
00:57:46,690 --> 00:57:48,010
It's perfect.

621
00:57:48,010 --> 00:57:51,290
Joo Haeng, you're the class president for a reason.

622
00:57:51,290 --> 00:57:53,200
Of course.

623
00:57:54,860 --> 00:57:56,430
Attention!

624
00:57:56,430 --> 00:57:59,760
Today, we'll be learning about Korean poems.

625
00:57:59,760 --> 00:58:02,360
Let's turn to page 171.

626
00:58:02,360 --> 00:58:03,590
- Class president!
- Yes?

627
00:58:03,590 --> 00:58:05,400
Wake him up.

628
00:58:06,720 --> 00:58:11,890
Never mind. Page 171. Class president, can you read it aloud?

629
00:58:11,890 --> 00:58:14,550
- These are some great friends.
- Yes.

630
00:58:21,180 --> 00:58:26,560
A day without Go Yoo Han was quiet, peaceful,

631
00:58:26,560 --> 00:58:29,020
and truthfully, boring.

632
00:58:33,850 --> 00:58:40,060
When Go Yoo Han was spitting nonsense, I was hoping he would go away.

633
00:58:40,060 --> 00:58:45,190
♫ Hug me so I’m not alone ♫

634
00:58:45,190 --> 00:58:48,620
♫ Hold me so I won’t fall ♫

635
00:58:48,620 --> 00:58:53,910
I'm feeling his absence only because I just got used to his presence.

636
00:58:53,910 --> 00:59:01,290
When I walked around the school field during lunchtime alone, it was so peaceful that it felt weird.

637
00:59:01,290 --> 00:59:07,200
I felt anxious like I was procrastinating or pushing something off.

638
00:59:07,200 --> 00:59:08,890
♫ Always be there for you ♫

639
00:59:08,890 --> 00:59:10,320
Yeon Woo

640
00:59:10,320 --> 00:59:11,780
Choi Yeon Woo

641
00:59:11,780 --> 00:59:13,830
My Yeon Woo

642
00:59:13,830 --> 00:59:16,370
My Yeon Woo is the most tender beef.
(T/N: he means that Yeon Woo is tender-hearted.)

643
00:59:16,370 --> 00:59:18,260
Have you ever played with color?

644
00:59:18,260 --> 00:59:19,890
No, I haven't. Why?

645
00:59:19,890 --> 00:59:26,930
♫ I'll find you no matter where you are
I never once forgot any of those days ♫

646
00:59:26,930 --> 00:59:30,560
How in the world do you play with color?

647
00:59:30,560 --> 00:59:33,220
Rather than never being able to see color again,

648
00:59:33,220 --> 00:59:36,680
I didn't like the feeling of loss the moment the colors started fading.

649
00:59:36,680 --> 00:59:38,660
What do I do if he leaves

650
00:59:38,660 --> 00:59:42,320
after forcing his way into my life?

651
00:59:42,320 --> 00:59:49,020
♫ When I close my eyes I hear your breathing ♫

652
00:59:49,020 --> 00:59:53,290
Let's go see an exhibit.

653
00:59:53,290 --> 00:59:59,930
♫ I’ll wait for you here every day ♫

654
01:00:02,140 --> 01:00:04,990
I really wanted to see this with you.

655
01:00:04,990 --> 01:00:06,990
Media art.

656
01:00:08,210 --> 01:00:13,940
Let me escort you to a world where the flowers become you, and you become the flowers.

657
01:00:13,940 --> 01:00:15,990
What are you talking about?

658
01:00:27,820 --> 01:00:33,200
Yeon Woo, we're going into the starlight now.

659
01:01:44,420 --> 01:01:47,550
Will it be okay if you pass out today?

660
01:01:47,550 --> 01:01:49,190
I won't pass out.

661
01:01:49,190 --> 01:01:52,470
Today, I'm going to bear it, no matter what.

662
01:01:52,470 --> 01:01:57,860
Okay. The world where the flowers become you and you become the flowers.

663
01:01:57,860 --> 01:02:00,390
I'll show it to you now.

664
01:03:38,740 --> 01:03:40,890
It's beautiful.

665
01:03:48,300 --> 01:03:54,580
♫ Oh I will be fine. You don’t have to worry ♫

666
01:03:54,580 --> 01:04:00,070
♫ The way you look at me, I think about you, again and again ♫

667
01:04:00,070 --> 01:04:05,550
♫ When our eyes meet, I am reborn ♫

668
01:04:05,550 --> 01:04:08,110
Even if I become dependent on the Probe,

669
01:04:08,110 --> 01:04:12,200
even if I become like the Monos on TV who do those heinous things,

670
01:04:12,200 --> 01:04:14,680
I still want to see colors.

671
01:04:14,680 --> 01:04:18,500
That's what I desire.

672
01:04:18,500 --> 01:04:23,930
♫ So you can be even more freer ♫

673
01:04:23,930 --> 01:04:30,350
♫ This time, this love. I’ll remember this moment I’m with you ♫

674
01:04:30,350 --> 01:04:36,280
♫ I’m crush on your eyes ♫

675
01:04:36,280 --> 01:04:43,950
♫ This time, this love. When the whole world shines on me ♫

676
01:04:43,950 --> 01:04:46,230
♫ I’ll find wherever you go ♫

677
01:04:46,230 --> 01:04:49,020
- How are you getting home?
- Me? I'm taking the bus.

678
01:04:49,020 --> 01:04:50,920
♫ Oh, oh ♫

679
01:04:50,920 --> 01:04:55,060
Thanks for taking me to the exhibit today.

680
01:04:55,060 --> 01:04:58,270
For finding the exhibit, for showing it to me.

681
01:04:58,270 --> 01:05:02,280
For standing by me, so that I can see the colors and explaining them to me.

682
01:05:04,030 --> 01:05:05,520
Get home safe.

683
01:05:05,520 --> 01:05:08,340
Can Probes read minds too?

684
01:05:08,340 --> 01:05:11,910
Hey, let's go home together.

685
01:05:11,910 --> 01:05:14,790
That's too much. No. Let's just pretend that I didn't hear it and go home.

686
01:05:14,790 --> 01:05:16,870
- Is your aunt home?
- No.

687
01:05:16,870 --> 01:05:19,210
What the— What did I just say?

688
01:05:19,210 --> 01:05:21,790
- Then what about your father?
- He isn't there.

689
01:05:21,790 --> 01:05:23,120
Then, it'll just be us?

690
01:05:23,120 --> 01:05:28,610
He knows... that I don't have a mother. How much do you know?

691
01:05:28,610 --> 01:05:31,070
Go Yoo Han.

692
01:05:31,070 --> 01:05:33,020
Say it.

693
01:05:34,300 --> 01:05:39,100
If I let you come over, will you grant me a wish?

694
01:05:39,100 --> 01:05:41,260
I'll grant any wish.

695
01:05:48,010 --> 01:05:50,950
What are you doing? Hurry up and open the door. I'm hungry.

696
01:05:50,950 --> 01:05:54,250
Let's eat ramen. I want to eat ramen.

697
01:05:54,250 --> 01:05:57,810
What is he talking about? Ramen? Oh my goodness.
(T/N: in Korea, the phrase "Wanna come over for ramen?" has an equivalent meaning to "Netflix and chill.")

698
01:05:57,810 --> 01:06:00,030
Hurry up and open it.

699
01:06:01,730 --> 01:06:06,940
Is this incredibly beautiful woman our Yeon Woo's mother?

700
01:06:10,750 --> 01:06:11,880
What are you doing?

701
01:06:11,880 --> 01:06:15,520
Nothing. The painting called for me.

702
01:06:17,010 --> 01:06:19,610
Yeon Woo, let's sit down

703
01:06:19,610 --> 01:06:21,720
and look at the painting.

704
01:06:26,210 --> 01:06:28,320
Mom

705
01:06:30,660 --> 01:06:33,030
disappeared four years ago.

706
01:06:33,030 --> 01:06:38,290
Honestly, I've seen the flyer.

707
01:06:38,290 --> 01:06:43,220
I thought she looked familiar, but it was because of you.

708
01:06:44,710 --> 01:06:46,470
I want to see this painting.

709
01:06:46,470 --> 01:06:51,360
I want to see the true colors of this painting that my father drew.

710
01:06:51,360 --> 01:06:52,820
That's my wish.

711
01:06:52,820 --> 01:06:56,700
Don't cry. I'll let you see it.

712
01:06:56,700 --> 01:06:59,190
That's why I came here.

713
01:07:15,490 --> 01:07:17,390
Yeon Woo.

714
01:07:20,370 --> 01:07:22,600
Just hold on a bit longer.

715
01:07:35,500 --> 01:07:37,860
Sky...

716
01:07:37,860 --> 01:07:40,380
Her sky blue dress.

717
01:07:41,920 --> 01:07:43,950
Mom...

718
01:07:46,530 --> 01:07:48,750
Her brown shoes.

719
01:07:49,660 --> 01:07:51,980
Red lips.

720
01:07:53,180 --> 01:07:56,130
Yellow....

721
01:07:56,130 --> 01:07:59,220
Your headband was yellow, Mom.

722
01:08:00,830 --> 01:08:04,240
This is how your true smile looked like.

723
01:08:04,240 --> 01:08:07,430
This is the aura you have.

724
01:08:07,430 --> 01:08:10,970
Where are you, Mom?

725
01:08:10,970 --> 01:08:14,230
I can tell you everything now.

726
01:08:14,230 --> 01:08:17,390
I can teach you the colors.

727
01:08:27,700 --> 01:08:31,640
Mom told me that

728
01:08:31,640 --> 01:08:34,040
we were looking at the same world.

729
01:08:34,040 --> 01:08:39,370
That the world wasn't gray, that it had beautiful colors.

730
01:08:42,390 --> 01:08:45,990
I'll become your color.

731
01:08:45,990 --> 01:08:48,420
I'm by your side.

732
01:08:49,460 --> 01:08:52,270
I'll become your color.

733
01:08:57,590 --> 01:09:02,790
Why are you so handsome?

734
01:09:30,830 --> 01:09:32,620
Yeon Woo,

735
01:09:33,750 --> 01:09:35,610
are you okay?

736
01:09:36,480 --> 01:09:38,490
Doesn't your head hurt?

737
01:09:38,490 --> 01:09:40,350
It hurts.

738
01:09:50,890 --> 01:09:55,000
Yeon Woo, stay behind me.

739
01:10:02,680 --> 01:10:04,670
Aunt!

740
01:10:04,670 --> 01:10:06,060
Aunt?

741
01:10:06,060 --> 01:10:08,180
Who's this kid?

742
01:10:23,420 --> 01:10:26,310
So this is what Aunt looks like...

743
01:10:32,320 --> 01:10:33,730
This kid...

744
01:10:33,730 --> 01:10:36,350
No violence! You can't use violence.

745
01:10:37,830 --> 01:10:39,680
What are you?

746
01:10:39,680 --> 01:10:41,950
I'm a friend from his class.

747
01:10:41,950 --> 01:10:44,440
A friend?

748
01:10:44,440 --> 01:10:46,450
A friend...

749
01:10:46,450 --> 01:10:47,640
Yes.

750
01:10:47,640 --> 01:10:49,180
We're not that close yet.

751
01:10:49,180 --> 01:10:51,680
Aunt, look at the uniform. It's the same, isn't it?

752
01:10:51,680 --> 01:10:54,750
- I'm Yeon Woo's one—
- Yeon Woo doesn't have any friends.

753
01:10:54,750 --> 01:10:55,780
Who are you?

754
01:10:55,780 --> 01:10:57,840
No, Aunt. I made a friend.

755
01:10:57,840 --> 01:10:59,840
He really is my friend.

756
01:11:00,960 --> 01:11:03,400
I'm the closest with Yeon Woo.

757
01:11:05,940 --> 01:11:11,060
See? It's a good thing you transferred schools. You made a friend.

758
01:11:11,060 --> 01:11:12,610
