01:33:39,010 --> 01:33:42,280
Yeon Woo, this isn't a dream.

1008
01:33:42,280 --> 01:33:44,640
We're going to leave now.

1009
01:33:44,640 --> 01:33:47,020
We're leaving this place that locked you in.

1010
01:33:47,020 --> 01:33:50,120
♫ I never once forgot any of those days ♫

1011
01:33:50,120 --> 01:33:55,350
♫ The words I kept to myself ♫

1012
01:33:55,350 --> 01:33:56,150
♫ I'm going... ♫

1013
01:33:56,150 --> 01:33:58,190
This all feels like a dream.

1014
01:33:58,190 --> 01:33:59,980
How many pills did you take?

1015
01:33:59,980 --> 01:34:02,280
♫ More than any words ♫

1016
01:34:02,280 --> 01:34:06,550
First, let's change.

1017
01:34:06,550 --> 01:34:09,670
♫ I hear your breathing ♫

1018
01:34:09,670 --> 01:34:13,770
♫ I’ll remember all your days ♫

1019
01:34:13,770 --> 01:34:20,760
♫ I’ll wait for you here every day ♫

1020
01:34:26,390 --> 01:34:28,600
It's real.

1021
01:34:29,720 --> 01:34:32,260
Did you wake up?

1022
01:34:32,260 --> 01:34:34,620
I think so.

1023
01:34:36,220 --> 01:34:38,510
I need to keep taking those pills...

1024
01:34:38,510 --> 01:34:42,630
Stop taking them. You have me now.

1025
01:34:50,870 --> 01:34:53,030
Where are we going right now?

1026
01:34:53,030 --> 01:34:54,950
To the ocean.

1027
01:34:54,950 --> 01:34:56,420
Why the ocean?

1028
01:34:56,420 --> 01:35:01,790
To show you the color you saw at the nurse's office.

1029
01:35:10,960 --> 01:35:15,040
That's the color of the ocean.

1030
01:35:15,040 --> 01:35:17,200
The color of the ocean...

1031
01:35:17,200 --> 01:35:20,760
The... color of the ocean...

1032
01:35:20,760 --> 01:35:23,990
Yes. The color of the ocean.

1033
01:35:34,180 --> 01:35:35,030
[Hilltop Hotel]

1034
01:35:35,030 --> 01:35:37,180
Wait... this isn't the ocean.

1035
01:35:37,180 --> 01:35:39,210
Well, the night is long.

1036
01:35:39,210 --> 01:35:40,630
- Let's go.
- Hum?

1037
01:35:40,630 --> 01:35:48,180
What?
[Comfortable | Clean | Cheap!]

1038
01:35:49,570 --> 01:35:57,060
I only thought about sharing a bed with you. This wasn't part of the plan.

1039
01:35:57,060 --> 01:35:59,650
That will never be an option.

1040
01:36:00,850 --> 01:36:05,790
If you're okay looking at me without a mask, doesn't that mean you like me?

1041
01:36:08,210 --> 01:36:10,980
Aren't you going to turn the lights off?

1042
01:36:10,980 --> 01:36:13,320
Fine, don't turn them off.

1043
01:36:13,320 --> 01:36:17,930
I'm fine looking at your face all night.

1044
01:36:17,930 --> 01:36:19,690
I'll turn it off.

1045
01:36:24,550 --> 01:36:28,990
Honestly, I like your color moving.

1046
01:36:28,990 --> 01:36:33,920
I like it when you reach out like a little kid when you see the colors.

1047
01:36:33,920 --> 01:36:37,720
When I teach you the colors, your lips open slightly,

1048
01:36:37,720 --> 01:36:39,900
and I like the excitement on your face.

1049
01:36:39,900 --> 01:36:45,150
I also like it when you get all defensive when teased and sigh as you let things be.

1050
01:36:45,150 --> 01:36:49,330
Even how easily you get provoked.

1051
01:36:49,330 --> 01:36:52,990
But, I couldn't tell you these things

1052
01:36:53,890 --> 01:36:57,080
because I felt like you would run away.

1053
01:37:01,400 --> 01:37:05,990
Whenever I saw you, you had an expression you couldn't hide.

1054
01:37:05,990 --> 01:37:11,420
It was the same expression trainees had right before they left the agency.

1055
01:37:11,420 --> 01:37:13,550
Let go of me!

1056
01:37:13,550 --> 01:37:15,800
Why are you acting like this?

1057
01:37:17,720 --> 01:37:20,810
I tried to stop having feelings for you

1058
01:37:20,810 --> 01:37:25,690
and acted like everything was fine to hide that fact.

1059
01:37:26,860 --> 01:37:29,220
Don't I have that same expression on my face right now, too?

1060
01:37:29,220 --> 01:37:30,760
What?

1061
01:37:31,790 --> 01:37:34,170
I ran away, Yeon Woo.

1062
01:37:34,170 --> 01:37:38,530
There's probably an uproar back home in Seoul.

1063
01:37:44,180 --> 01:37:47,860
What are you talking about? Did you leave your agency?

1064
01:37:47,860 --> 01:37:51,650
I don't want to debut.

1065
01:37:54,060 --> 01:37:56,220
Because of me...

1066
01:38:00,310 --> 01:38:05,030
It's not because of you. It's something I've been thinking about for a while now.

1067
01:38:05,030 --> 01:38:09,200
I was so busy thinking about myself that I never once thought about

1068
01:38:09,200 --> 01:38:12,330
your worries, your future, and your life.

1069
01:38:12,330 --> 01:38:15,690
- Not even once?
- No.

1070
01:38:15,690 --> 01:38:19,860
How could you run away, though? Are you really okay with this?

1071
01:38:19,860 --> 01:38:21,320
As you can see,

1072
01:38:21,320 --> 01:38:25,990
to save you, Yeon Woo, who has never once thought about my life,

1073
01:38:25,990 --> 01:38:29,500
I went to the hospital even when I'm on the run.

1074
01:38:29,500 --> 01:38:31,730
With that being said, let's sleep in the same—

1075
01:38:31,730 --> 01:38:33,420
Sorry!

1076
01:38:34,710 --> 01:38:37,260
After hitting me again, you're only sorry?

1077
01:38:37,260 --> 01:38:41,340
But... we can't sleep in the same bed.

1078
01:38:42,200 --> 01:38:43,990
Why?

1079
01:38:44,780 --> 01:38:48,630
I... don't know.

1080
01:38:56,940 --> 01:39:01,020
That's right. We're both on the run.

1081
01:39:01,020 --> 01:39:04,630
Still, we'll see the ocean tomorrow for the first time as a couple.

1082
01:39:07,490 --> 01:39:09,390
Sleep well.

1083
01:39:24,380 --> 01:39:28,360
When I was younger, I didn't understand the concept of foam.

1084
01:39:28,360 --> 01:39:30,340
Really?

1085
01:39:30,340 --> 01:39:34,870
But as I got older, I realized it was just a bunch of bubbles.

1086
01:39:34,870 --> 01:39:39,170
There's probably more of those, right?

1087
01:39:39,170 --> 01:39:41,480
Things that seem like something but are meaningless.

1088
01:39:41,480 --> 01:39:46,060
Nothing's meaningless when I'm with you.

1089
01:39:46,060 --> 01:39:47,260
You're so cheesy.

1090
01:39:47,260 --> 01:39:49,520
Cheesy?

1091
01:40:00,900 --> 01:40:05,910
♫ Hug me so I’m not alone ♫

1092
01:40:05,910 --> 01:40:09,670
♫ Hold me so I won’t fall ♫

1093
01:40:09,670 --> 01:40:12,840
What color is this ocean?

1094
01:40:12,840 --> 01:40:14,410
Right now?

1095
01:40:14,410 --> 01:40:16,980
Colors don't ever stay the same.

1096
01:40:16,980 --> 01:40:18,790
Like you?

1097
01:40:19,710 --> 01:40:23,010
No. Like you.

1098
01:40:23,010 --> 01:40:26,140
♫ I’ll remember ♫

1099
01:40:26,140 --> 01:40:31,670
Go Yoo Han's eyes are usually caramel-colored, but there are times they shine brightly

1100
01:40:31,670 --> 01:40:36,010
and times they fall into a darker shade.

1101
01:40:36,010 --> 01:40:39,000
Wouldn't that be the same for the ocean?

1102
01:40:39,000 --> 01:40:43,190
Over there. That dark blue color is cobalt blue.

1103
01:40:43,190 --> 01:40:46,900
The blackish-blue in the middle is Prussian blue.

1104
01:40:46,900 --> 01:40:51,130
Over there. That purplish blue is indigo blue.

1105
01:40:51,130 --> 01:40:56,150
Due to its mysteriousness, cobalt blue was often used by Renaissance artists

1106
01:40:56,150 --> 01:41:01,890
and indigo blue was often used to dye fabric because people liked the color.

1107
01:41:01,890 --> 01:41:03,480
What about the Prussian blue in the middle?

1108
01:41:03,480 --> 01:41:05,100
It's the first synthetic pigment.

1109
01:41:05,100 --> 01:41:07,980
A chemist in Berlin made the color by accident.

1110
01:41:07,980 --> 01:41:12,290
But thanks to him, many can use it because it's cheap.

1111
01:41:12,290 --> 01:41:16,110
That's right. You said blue was very valuable... because of lapis lazuli.

1112
01:41:16,110 --> 01:41:17,790
I have one at home.

1113
01:41:17,790 --> 01:41:20,240
I'll definitely show you sometime later.

1114
01:41:20,240 --> 01:41:23,480
I would love to see it.

1115
01:41:25,780 --> 01:41:27,670
Are there a lot of shades of blue?

1116
01:41:27,670 --> 01:41:31,690
It has the most shades out of all because blue is a popular color.

1117
01:41:31,690 --> 01:41:36,060
The shades that are named after an everyday object are: blue, teal,

1118
01:41:36,060 --> 01:41:38,050
water blue, sky blue,

1119
01:41:38,050 --> 01:41:41,350
cyan, cerulean blue, pastel blue,

1120
01:41:41,350 --> 01:41:43,530
powder blue, sky gray,

1121
01:41:43,530 --> 01:41:46,620
ocean blue, mint, Prussian blue,

1122
01:41:46,620 --> 01:41:51,220
indigo blue, cobalt blue, sapphire, navy.

1123
01:41:51,220 --> 01:41:53,830
There are other shades like azurite blue,

1124
01:41:53,830 --> 01:41:55,750
ultramarine, azure,

1125
01:41:55,750 --> 01:41:59,390
royal blue, French turquoise, turquoise,

1126
01:41:59,390 --> 01:42:01,820
empire blue, Indian blue,

1127
01:42:01,820 --> 01:42:04,260
aqua blue, marine blue,

1128
01:42:04,260 --> 01:42:06,720
lavender blue, Prussian blue,

1129
01:42:06,720 --> 01:42:09,030
Egyptian blue, Matisse blue,

1130
01:42:09,030 --> 01:42:11,840
lapis lazuli, majolica blue,

1131
01:42:11,840 --> 01:42:14,480
midnight blue, moonlight blue,

1132
01:42:14,480 --> 01:42:16,830
navy blue, Nile blue,

1133
01:42:16,830 --> 01:42:18,910
Spode blue, saxe blue,

1134
01:42:18,910 --> 01:42:20,670
Versailles.

1135
01:42:20,670 --> 01:42:22,860
What?

1136
01:42:22,860 --> 01:42:25,530
Why? Was there something strange among them?

1137
01:42:25,530 --> 01:42:27,680
There's still a lot of shades left.

1138
01:42:27,680 --> 01:42:33,660
Well... I thought I heard a word that didn't belong among the blues.

1139
01:42:33,660 --> 01:42:36,410
Which one?

1140
01:42:36,410 --> 01:42:41,780
Color names can come from people, regions,

1141
01:42:41,780 --> 01:42:43,660
and even countries.

1142
01:42:43,660 --> 01:42:47,020
I don't get which one seems misplaced.

1143
01:42:47,020 --> 01:42:49,070
- You said "sex" blue.
- Right.
(T/N: he's talking about saxe blue. They sound the same but have a different spelling.)

1144
01:42:49,070 --> 01:42:52,220
That's the actual name?

1145
01:42:52,220 --> 01:42:56,140
It's named after Saxony, a state along Germany's Elbe River.

1146
01:42:56,140 --> 01:42:59,760
Sa-xe bl-ue.

1147
01:42:59,760 --> 01:43:05,300
S-a-x-e  b-l-u-e

1148
01:43:05,300 --> 01:43:08,490
- Oh, it's named after a region.
- Yeah.

1149
01:43:08,490 --> 01:43:11,080
It was a good approach.

1150
01:43:11,080 --> 01:43:16,150
Out of the seven deadly sins in Christianity, blue is said to symbolize lust.

1151
01:43:16,150 --> 01:43:18,460
So sex blue could exist.

1152
01:43:18,460 --> 01:43:23,320
Yeon Woo, what do you think? Could that be my color?

1153
01:43:23,320 --> 01:43:27,650
I didn't know there could be this many shades of blue.

1154
01:43:27,650 --> 01:43:32,490
The world of color is as infinite as one's love for another.

1155
01:43:32,490 --> 01:43:35,420
Go Yoo Han, how did you memorize all of these?

1156
01:43:35,420 --> 01:43:36,850
Is that the end?

1157
01:43:36,850 --> 01:43:42,190
There's probably more if I search, but that's all I memorized.

1158
01:43:42,190 --> 01:43:44,630
That's amazing. How did you memorize all of these?

1159
01:43:44,630 --> 01:43:50,000
I can remember them all when I just think of you. All I want is to teach them to you.

1160
01:43:50,000 --> 01:43:51,710
♫ The words I kept to myself ♫

1161
01:43:51,710 --> 01:43:56,160
♫ I'm going to confess to you now ♫

1162
01:43:56,160 --> 01:44:03,210
♫ More than any words, when I close my eyes ♫

1163
01:44:03,210 --> 01:44:04,700
♫  I hear your breathing  ♫

1164
01:44:04,700 --> 01:44:07,700
Why are you looking at me when you should be looking at the ocean?

1165
01:44:07,700 --> 01:44:10,520
It feels like a dream when I look at you.

1166
01:44:10,520 --> 01:44:12,730
That's what I wanted to say.

1167
01:44:12,730 --> 01:44:17,610
But he said it first.

1168
01:44:20,840 --> 01:44:23,210
- Do you think there's a payphone here?
- Why?

1169
01:44:23,210 --> 01:44:24,920
I'm going to call my aunt.

1170
01:44:24,920 --> 01:44:27,680
If I don't, she might die from worrying.

1171
01:44:27,680 --> 01:44:29,930
Let's do that then.

1172
01:44:29,930 --> 01:44:32,850
Don't worry.

1173
01:44:32,850 --> 01:44:36,300
What? Really?

1174
01:44:36,300 --> 01:44:39,880
Then, Yoo Han—

1175
01:44:43,450 --> 01:44:45,310
I understand.

1176
01:44:45,310 --> 01:44:47,660
I said I understand!

1177
01:44:57,560 --> 01:44:59,230
What's wrong?

1178
01:44:59,230 --> 01:45:01,560
Why are you acting like this?

1179
01:45:01,560 --> 01:45:03,060
Go back to Seoul quickly.

1180
01:45:03,060 --> 01:45:05,150
Was your aunt really angry?

1181
01:45:05,150 --> 01:45:09,210
It's not my family but yours.

1182
01:45:09,210 --> 01:45:11,810
- Is your mom a congresswoman?
- Yes.

1183
01:45:11,810 --> 01:45:14,820
Your older sister is a judge, your older brother is a military officer,

1184
01:45:14,820 --> 01:45:16,280
and your dad's the chairman of Taejong Group?

1185
01:45:16,280 --> 01:45:18,360
Yes, they are.

1186
01:45:20,490 --> 01:45:22,090
What?

1187
01:45:22,090 --> 01:45:25,180
I'm hungry!

1188
01:45:25,180 --> 01:45:27,410
Buy me.

1189
01:45:36,090 --> 01:45:40,290
If you don't return by today, they're going to report me as your kidnapper.

1190
01:45:40,290 --> 01:45:43,760
The political world, the financial world, and the military world. Is there something like that?

1191
01:45:43,760 --> 01:45:47,480
Anyway, it seems they are all ready for action.

1192
01:45:47,480 --> 01:45:53,450
According to my aunt, the situation seemed like there was an arrest warrant in place for the Mono who kidnapped his Probe.

1193
01:45:53,450 --> 01:45:54,750
So, how can you eat?

1194
01:45:54,750 --> 01:45:58,150
In a situation like this, we need to eat to gain strength.

1195
01:45:58,150 --> 01:45:59,960
Okay.

1196
01:45:59,960 --> 01:46:01,880
You should eat a lot.

1197
01:46:01,880 --> 01:46:03,630
Here you go.

1198
01:46:09,690 --> 01:46:13,620
I couldn't reach you, and you didn't show up to school, so I asked,

1199
01:46:13,620 --> 01:46:17,990
and your aunt told me you will be transferring because you were very obsessed with me.

1200
01:46:17,990 --> 01:46:22,950
The congresswoman in my family thinks that since you may have a plan to kidnap me,

1201
01:46:22,950 --> 01:46:25,850
she'll stop you from approaching me.

1202
01:46:25,850 --> 01:46:31,030
So I thought about it... and there's only one answer.

1203
01:46:33,400 --> 01:46:36,480
Finding me and running away?

1204
01:46:36,480 --> 01:46:39,600
So that's how we ended up like this.

1205
01:46:39,600 --> 01:46:43,920
But, it's dangerous for a Probe to be around a Mono.

1206
01:46:43,920 --> 01:46:47,550
Both your mom and my aunt are right.

1207
01:46:47,550 --> 01:46:50,590
I shouldn't be allowed to be around you.

1208
01:46:50,590 --> 01:46:51,850
That's what is right.

1209
01:46:51,850 --> 01:46:56,620
A restraining order is only for when both parties are alive.

1210
01:46:56,620 --> 01:47:00,930
Who cares about that when you were willing to die for me?

1211
01:47:00,930 --> 01:47:02,620
I like you.

1212
01:47:02,620 --> 01:47:09,060
But, I'll obsess over you, I'll doubt you,

1213
01:47:09,060 --> 01:47:12,770
and end up killing you.

1214
01:47:14,170 --> 01:47:15,800
It's right to stay away from me.

1215
01:47:15,800 --> 01:47:20,790
Yeon Woo, do you want to know a secret?

1216
01:47:23,030 --> 01:47:27,630
The truth is I can't identify people's faces.

1217
01:47:27,630 --> 01:47:32,750
I have prosopagnosia, a condition that prevents me from even recognizing Jung Joo Haeng, a friend since elementary school.
(T/N: prosopagnosia is a neurological condition characterized by the inability to recognize the faces of familiar people.)

1218
01:47:34,280 --> 01:47:36,700
That's me.

1219
01:47:36,700 --> 01:47:41,200
I was smart though, so I was able to distinguish them

1220
01:47:41,200 --> 01:47:45,890
by their voice, gaits, clothes, and habits.

1221
01:48:02,590 --> 01:48:06,620
But, I was able to tell you apart.

1222
01:48:13,090 --> 01:48:17,430
It was the first time I could distinguish someone's face.

1223
01:48:22,490 --> 01:48:28,850
When our eyes meet, and I see your color moving, I can recognize you.

1224
01:48:28,850 --> 01:48:32,150
♫ You don’t have to worry ♫

1225
01:48:32,150 --> 01:48:37,820
♫ The way you look at me, I think about you again and again ♫

1226
01:48:37,820 --> 01:48:44,070
♫ When our eyes meet, I am reborn ♫

1227
01:48:44,070 --> 01:48:50,260
♫ It feels like the whole world is spreading
Yeah, just like a picture ♫

1228
01:48:50,260 --> 01:48:56,150
♫ Take my hand, I’ll let you go ♫

1229
01:48:56,150 --> 01:49:01,790
♫ So you can be even more freer ♫

1230
01:49:01,790 --> 01:49:02,680
♫ This time, this love ♫

1231
01:49:02,680 --> 01:49:05,420
So that's why you wanted to see my color moving.

1232
01:49:05,420 --> 01:49:08,190
♫ I’ll remember this moment I’m with you ♫

1233
01:49:08,190 --> 01:49:14,050
♫ I’m crush on your eyes ♫

1234
01:49:14,050 --> 01:49:15,300
♫ This time, this love ♫

1235
01:49:15,300 --> 01:49:18,690
When you look at me... when you look at me...

1236
01:49:18,690 --> 01:49:23,690
when you face me, your eyes whisper to me.

1237
01:49:23,690 --> 01:49:25,790
They whisper to me.

1238
01:49:25,790 --> 01:49:31,290
Then, I can picture your face, and that face is what I see.

1239
01:49:31,290 --> 01:49:39,040
When you're not around, I picture you over and over again. Hundreds, thousands, tens of thousands of times.

1240
01:49:39,040 --> 01:49:42,320
But I can't recognize you when I do that.

1241
01:49:42,320 --> 01:49:46,300
But as soon as I see you, I can be sure

1242
01:49:46,300 --> 01:49:47,280
♫ On meaningless days ♫

1243
01:49:47,280 --> 01:49:50,490
that you're Choi Yeon Woo.

1244
01:49:50,490 --> 01:49:52,970
Telling me that I'm the only one he can distinguish.

1245
01:49:52,970 --> 01:49:58,460
The fact that he can't picture my face when we're apart.

1246
01:49:58,460 --> 01:49:59,930
The reason why he told me not to run away from him.

1247
01:50:00,000 --> 01:50:03,850
Why I can't run from him.

1248
01:50:03,850 --> 01:50:07,500
It explains everything.

1249
01:50:07,500 --> 01:50:10,090
I can't picture colors without you either.

1250
01:50:10,090 --> 01:50:15,610
You're one of a kind to me too.
(T/N: his name, Go Yoo Han, means unique.)

